                  <persName id="t18190915-122-person1144">
                  ANN 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18190915-122-person1144" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-122-person1144" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-122-person1144" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of 
               <persName id="t18190915-122-person1145">
                  Joseph 
                  William Smith
               <interp inst="t18190915-122-person1145" type="surname" value="William Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-122-person1145" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-122-person1145" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 9th of August, about eight o'clock in the morning, I found the prisoner in my front room, with the watch in his hand. I asked him for it, he resisted, and would not give it to me. I laid hold of him; he pulled me out of the street-door, and knocked me down. I got up, and pursued, calling Stop thief! he was stopped a quarter of a mile off with it in his hand. I never lost sight of him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190915-122-person1146">
                  JOHN 
                  NEEKS
               <interp inst="t18190915-122-person1146" type="surname" value="NEEKS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-122-person1146" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-122-person1146" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard the alarm, and stopped the prisoner, who was running. He said,</p>
               <p>"Don't stop me, it is not me." I found the watch in his hand.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
